  "vulnerability_information": "Libcurl connection reuse for cleartext-upgrade mail protocols does not include the later transfer's CURLOPT_USE_SSL. If a plaintext connection to one of these protocols is already open and reusable, a later transfer that explicitly requires STARTTLS can incorrectly reuse that plaintext connection.\n\nThis affects smtp://, pop3://, and imap://\n\n## Reproduction\nStart the server:\n\n```bash\npython3 ./server.py --port 2525\n```\n\nControl:\n\n```bash\ncurl -sv \\\n  -u alice:pw \\\n  --url 'imap://127.0.0.1:2525/Box/;MAILINDEX=1' \\\n  --ssl-reqd\n```\n\nReuse:\n\n```bash\ncurl -sv \\\n  -u alice:pw \\\n  --url 'imap://127.0.0.1:2525/' \\\n  -X NOOP \\\n  --next \\\n  -sv \\\n  -u alice:pw \\\n  --url 'imap://127.0.0.1:2525/Box/;MAILINDEX=1' \\\n  --ssl-reqd\n```\n\n## Impact\n\nA later TLS-required mail transfer can be sent over a previously established plaintext connection, contrary to expectation.",
